# SOUL.md
#
# This file gives heartbeat-gateway the operator context it needs to classify
# incoming events. The classifier reads the FIRST 500 CHARACTERS, so put your
# most important context at the top.
#
# Three sections drive classification accuracy:
#
#   ## Current Focus  — what the agent is actively working on right now
#   ## Projects       — list of active and planned projects with status
#   ## Watch          — explicit escalation rules and alert thresholds
#
# Copy this file to ~/workspace/SOUL.md (or wherever GATEWAY_SOUL_MD_PATH points)
# and edit it to match your current work.

## Current Focus

Phase 5: Production hardening. Active branch: feature/retry-logic.
Goal: wire up dead-letter queue and add retry middleware before beta launch.
Blocking: DLQ schema needs sign-off from Alice before proceeding.

## Projects

- heartbeat-gateway (active — beta launch target: 2025-02-01)
- openclaw (planning — blocked on heartbeat-gateway shipping)
- vikingbot (paused — resume after openclaw foundation complete)

## Watch

Escalate immediately:
- CI failure on `main` in heartbeat-gateway
- Linear issue with label "blocked" assigned to me
- PostHog error spike > 50 occurrences

Do NOT escalate:
- CI failures on feature branches (expected during development)
- Linear comments on completed issues
- PostHog pageview events
